&lt;h1&gt;Urbanist & Assistant Professor&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Urban Data for Design — TU Delft&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
  I am &lt;strong&gt;Daniele Cannatella&lt;/strong&gt;, Assistant Professor in &lt;em&gt;Urban Data for Design&lt;/em&gt; 
  at the Faculty of Architecture and the Built Environment, &lt;strong&gt;TU Delft&lt;/strong&gt;, Department of Urbanism.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
  My work bridges &lt;strong&gt;spatial analytics&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;climate adaptation&lt;/strong&gt;, 
  and &lt;strong&gt;landscape-based regional design&lt;/strong&gt; to support evidence-based planning and design 
  for resilient and sustainable cities.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
  I collaborate with &lt;strong&gt;municipalities&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;research institutions&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;students&lt;/strong&gt; 
  to develop strategies that combine analytical rigor with design innovation.
&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;img src="images/portrait.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded-circle shadow" alt="Daniele Cannatella"&gt;






